text1: A ship devoid of any identifying markings bearing a technologically advanced systems and evidently designed specifically for combat with a subfocus on exploration and self sufficiency. The Vengeance possesses powerful sensors and an efficient logistics profile coupled with strong shields, a large hangar, and a variety of long ranged combat options. Much of the technology on this vessel is rare or unknown to the sector, baring large variable intensity laser banks of unknown design, a non antimatter propulsion system, a compliment of photon torpedos, and a variety of enmities usually deemed too frivolous aboard combat craft, such as holodecks and food synthesizers. In fact, the deeper one looks into this vessel the more apparent it becomes that, despite a requiring a large manufacturing base to have even been made, it is clearly not of this sector and, if pre collapse technical development is any indication, likely not of this galaxy either. Unfortunately, its databanks have been nearly entirely scrubbed clean and the lack of any living members of its former crew means that the question of its origins will likely remain unanswered.
